This is a simple plate that i made at the photography course by @yehiaelalaily with @phlog___ at @consoleya , it is a smoked salmon with baby artichoke, oranges, gooseberries and corn and all paired with a spicy pepper dressing that combines all the flavors together. It was such an honor to work with yehia again and i always find excitement with working with him and seeing my work under the spotlight of his lens. Also phlog created a very nice course that made the students try to shoot several scenes including my plate, also the amazing space that inspired me a lot at consolya with the very romantic moldings and the wall art surrounding us everywhere.
.
.
.
.
.

another dish that was made on the food photography course with @yehiaelalaily , @phlog___ at @consoleya . this is spicy corn and mango gazpacho paired with butter poached baby corn, sweet corn, mangos and sprinkle of tajin on top... i was inspired from @peri.fooding @graciaseg spicy mango drink and i decided to add the corn and make it a gazpacho... it is a very interesting dish mixed with flavors of sweetness, savory and spiciness in a very harmonically balanced way.

This is a very summery refreshing recipe…. A white beans with lemon dip that will bring summer to your mouth.
Ingredients: 
- olive oil
- 200 gm soaked white beans
- pinch of salt
- black pepper to taste
- pinch of paprika
- pinch of chili flakes 
- drizzle of honey
- tsp of chili jam
- the juice of 4 lemons
- the zest of 2 lemons
And for garnish some paprika and some lemon zest as well.
الوصفة دى من الوصفات المنعشة فى الصيف… غموس الفاصوليا البيضاء مع الليمون.
المكونات:
- زيت زيتون
- ٢٠٠ جرام فاصوليا بيضاء منقوعة
- رشة ملح
- فلفل اسود حسب الرغبة
- بابريكا
- فلفل حامى مطحون 
- عسل
- مربى الفلفل الحار
- عصير اربع ليمونات
- قشر ليمونتان
و للتزيين يتم رش بعض البابريكا و قشور الليمون.
It is definitely worth a try and you should definitely give it a go. Enjoy.

This an easy recipe…but very delicious indeed… only the adventurous will try this haha..
I don’t eat span but i had an alternative to it so i figured why not.. and here we are with the fake spam and the soy cured egg yolks.
The mirin you can substitute with 1 tsp of honey with 1/2 tsp of rice vinegar.
For a jammy yolk leave it curing for 12 hours if more it will be jelly candy like and if less it will be runnier yolks. Don’t worry curing is a method of cooking so it is not raw.
You should use good quality of yolks not any egg yolks. 
Have fun guys and explore other flavors and techniques from around the world.

Let’s make the best korean tteokbokki or at least my version of it… it is sooo good that you will make it at least twice a week hahahaha specially the korean series fans will definitely love this one.. INGREDIENTS:
- tteokbokki sticks (from any asian market or from @zumrafood )
- cocktail hotdogs 
- green onions
- 2.5 tbsp tomato paste 
- 1 tsp chili powder 
- 1 tsp paprika
- 1.5 tsp sriracha 
- 2 tsp honey 
- any type of cheese (i used mixed cheddar)
You have to try this one cause you will love it.. it is delicious and easy to make.

Wings are fun, so let’s make it a party….
Let’s make spicy honey mustard wings, truly one of the best wings ever.
Ingredients:
- chicken wings (duh)
- salt and pepper to taste
- cajun spice (tbsp)
- garlic powder (1 tsp)
- onion powder (1 tsp)
- 1 egg white (don’t use the yolk this way it will be much crispier)
- starch (3 tbsp)
For the sauce:
- 1 tbsp mustard 
- 1 tsp sriracha 
- 2 tsp honey
And you can garnish with whatever you like i chose chili flakes.
Have fun guys it is a very easy recipe and it is like a party in your mouth, so enjoy the process.
#chickenwings #wings #recipe #honeymustard #spicyhoney #partyfood #foodrecipe #thefoodguy #thefoodguycooks #marwanhazem #marwanhazemcooks #theweekend #funrecipe

In collaboration with the embassy of Thailand and Oscar hyper market to celebrate the rice festival (15 September to 21 September) i made this beautiful recipe…. Thai fried rice with shrimps and pineapple.
This is a very easy recipe but has a ton of flavor… enjoy.
Ingredients:
- shrimps
- Thai jasmine rice (chilled)
- 2 eggs
- sesame oil
- pineapple 
- vegetables (any kind you like)
- oyster sauce 
- fish sauce
- soy sauce
- green onions.
الوصفة دى انا عملتها بالتعاون مع سفارة تايلانند و اوسكار هايبر ماركت احتفالا بمهرجان الرز اللى هيبتدى يوم ١٥ و يستمر لحد يوم ٢١ سبتمبر و عملت رز الياسمين التايلاندى بالجمبرى و الاناناس و هى وصفة لذيذة جدا و سهلة.
#think_rice_think_thailand

This is a traditional alexandrian recipe (as i know) that is really famous in our culture… yellow lentils with rice (i used jasmine rice ) and tiger skin eggs (which is بيض مدحرج) it is so easy and fast that it literally takes no time or effort to make yet it is really delicious and fulfilling… it need no special ingredients at all just love and some simple ingredients with it. 
دى وصفة تقليدية من الاسكندرية و اسمها كشرى عدس اصفر بالبيض المدحرج و هى وصفة سهلة و لذيذة جدا و حقيقي مش بتاخد وقت نهائي فى التحضير و سهلة و سريعة و مريحة جدا اتمنى تعجبكوا و تجربوها.
#think_rice_think_thailand  #marwancooks #thefoodguy #thefoodguycooks #chefmarwanhazem

Who doesn’t have the memory of seafood on the weekend… i think we all do, so i made it in a very very easy way to have this nostalgic treat as fast and easy as possible… i used jasmine rice because it always fluffy and soft with the caramelization of the onions and the saltiness of the fish and the tanginess of the pickled tomatoes what else can we ask for… enjoy it to the max guys.
مين فينا معندوش الذكري بتاعة اكلة السمك فى اخر الاسبوع اكيد كلنا عندنا الذكرى اللذيذة دى… انا بقى عملتلكوا الوجبة دى بكل بساطة و سهولة و سرعة كمان و استخدمت رز الياسمين التايلاندي عشان دايما بيطلع معايا مفرفر و هش و لذيذ و كمان مع كرملة البصل و الطعم السمك المتبل بالتوم و الكمون و كمان الطماطم المخللة كل دة بيعمل وجبة ممتعة و مليانة ذكريات. اعملوها و استمتعوا بيها.
#think_rice_think_thailand #marwancooks #marwanhazemcooks #thefoodguy #thefoodguycooks #marwanhazem #chefmarwanhazem #nostalgia #nostalgicfood #memories

I am partially back haha… this is a simple dish that has a good cut of steak with grilled onions, morel mushroom and micro sunflower greens with some sprinkles of calendula flowers and all paired with a very umami rich mushrooms broth that is made with morels, shiitake and porcini mushrooms. 
I know i have been away but i had such a huge mental block that made me trapped in a comfort zone that i didn’t like but i guess i am getting back step by step.
.
.
.
.
.

I wanted to make a simple dish that could have a small hint of peru so i decided to make shrimps that is butter poached and seared for tiny bit and paired with an olive coffee quenelle in the middle and topped with some sunflower microgreens all on a bed of two ways corn (with butter and roasted for crunch) and tomatoes with pickled onions (also two types of onions) and all with toasted simple bread made from corn flour and toasted till crunchy.. a very cool dish that is simple yet a bit complex but delicious in the end.
.

.
.

This is an easy recipe that can be done on a weekday easily with no hassle at all.. but let me talk to you about the skillet or lets say the cast iron skillet and it’s beneficial to our lives..
- Holds heat well: which means it gives an even doneness to the whole recipe and it gives an amazing full sear to your beef or chicken.
- Works well with many heat sources: as you saw in the video i used it on an induction and it worked perfectly.. it is also safe on any heat source and even in the oven.
- Easy to clean: it is not a hassle once you know the steps and i will show you in an up coming reel soon.
- it looks really cool for cooking and serving too specially if you used on the stove then popped it in the oven it will definitely look cool on your table.
Try the recipe and enjoy the cast iron skillets from @grifcookware because they offer amazing prices.
#castironskillet #grifcookware #grifcastiron #cookwithmarwan #marwanhazem #marwanhazemcooks #thefoodguy #thefoodguycooks #beef #preservedlemons
